@startuml engine-routing-and-connectors
title SafeCrowd Engine Routing and Connectors Boundary

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "domain" {
  class FacilityLayout {
    rooms
    doors
    connectors
  }

  class ConnectorSpec {
    kind
    endpoints
    base traversal rule계단, 램프, 에스컬레이터, 보행로처럼 층간 또는 구간 연결이 필요한 경우 connector와 modifier를 함께 확정할 수 있다. 
  }

  class ConnectorModifier {
    speed factor
    queue bias
    access rule
  }

  class StaticObstruction {
    geometry
    clearance effect
  }

  class DynamicObstacleRule {
    trigger window
    blocked area
  }

  class MeasurementRegionSpec {
    region geometry
    metric set
  }

  class RouteChoicePolicy {
    policy id
  }

  class PathCostModel {
    travel / queue / remaining cost
  }

  class RoutingTopologySnapshot {
    room graph
    door graph
    connector edges
  }
}

package "engine" {
  class EngineWorld {
    resources
    commands
  }

  class NavigationGraph {
    nodes
    edges
  }

  class TravelCostEvaluator {
    dynamic weights
  }

  class DynamicObstacleField {
    blocked segments
    active penalties
  }

  class ConnectorTraversalState {
    queue state
    throughput state
  }

  class PathPlannerSystem {
    path query
    reroute update
  }

  class FlowMeasurementService {
    region samplers
    door counters
    room counters
  }

  class MeasurementSample {
    time stamp
    metric values
  }
}

FacilityLayout --> RoutingTopologySnapshot : compile validated topology
ConnectorSpec *-- ConnectorModifier
FacilityLayout *-- ConnectorSpec
FacilityLayout *-- StaticObstruction
FacilityLayout *-- DynamicObstacleRule
FacilityLayout *-- MeasurementRegionSpec
RouteChoicePolicy --> PathCostModel

RoutingTopologySnapshot --> NavigationGraph : load as resource
RoutingTopologySnapshot --> ConnectorTraversalState : seed connector rules
DynamicObstacleRule --> DynamicObstacleField : runtime activation
PathCostModel --> TravelCostEvaluator : configure weights
DynamicObstacleField --> TravelCostEvaluator : penalty source
NavigationGraph --> TravelCostEvaluator

PathPlannerSystem --> NavigationGraph
PathPlannerSystem --> TravelCostEvaluator
PathPlannerSystem --> ConnectorTraversalState
FlowMeasurementService --> MeasurementSample
MeasurementRegionSpec --> FlowMeasurementService : register measurement regions
ConnectorTraversalState --> FlowMeasurementService : door / connector throughput
EngineWorld --> NavigationGraph
EngineWorld --> DynamicObstacleField
EngineWorld --> ConnectorTraversalState
EngineWorld --> FlowMeasurementService

note bottom of RoutingTopologySnapshot
  The engine should not depend on rich domain objects directly.
  Domain compiles a stable routing snapshot and
  registers that snapshot as engine resources.
end note

note bottom of DynamicObstacleField
  Static obstruction is baked into the topology first.
  Dynamic obstacle rules update a separate runtime field
  so path cost and access control can change over time
  without rebuilding the whole graph every frame.
end note

note bottom of FlowMeasurementService
  Measurement is treated as a boundary service.
  It emits domain-neutral samples that later become
  DoorHistory / RoomHistory / MeasurementRegionSeries.
end note

@enduml
